title: Nevada must hold a GOP presidential primary, despite a party-run caucus occurring 2 days later
description: The Nevada GOP saying they’ll only honor the results of their party-run caucus.

title: Smith & Wesson celebrates new headquarters opening in gun-friendly Tennessee
description: The company built a new 650,000-square foot headquarters in Tennessee.

title: The auto workers' strike enters its 4th week. The union president urges members to keep up the fight
description: The auto workers' strike is entering its 4th week.

title: Gov. Newsom vetoes bill that would have decriminalized psychedelic mushrooms
description: California Gov. Gavin Newsom has vetoed a bill aimed at decriminalizing the possession and use of some hallucinogens, including psychedelic mushrooms

title: At least 100 dead after powerful earthquakes strike western Afghanistan: UN
description: At least 100 people are dead and at least 500 injured after powerful earthquakes struck western Afghanistan on Saturday, the United Nations said.

title: At least 15 people are killed when a bomb brought home by children explodes in eastern Congo
description: A group of children brought home an explosive device they found while playing.

title: $1.4 billion Powerball jackpot prize up for grabs
description: Saturday night's Powerball Jackpot prize has risen to $1.4 billion. The last jackpot prize won was won on July 19.

title: US Senate leader raises trade and fentanyl at start of 1st congressional visit to China since 2019
description: U.S. doesn't want to cut economic ties with China but seeks level playing field.

title: Witnesses to FBI hunt for Civil War gold describe heavily loaded armored truck, signs of a night dig
description: New eyewitness accounts raise questions about the FBI’s secretive 2018 dig.

title: Israel live updates: Netanyahu says 'we're at war'
description: At least 22 people have died and more than 500 people have been injured after rockets were fired from Gaza into Israel by Hamas militants.

title: WATCH:  Thousands of rockets fired as Hamas militants target Israel
description: Thousands of rockets were fired Saturday morning as Hamas militants in Gaza targeted Israel, prompting Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu to say "we are at war."

title: Rockets fired from Gaza into Tel Aviv and Jerusalem as Hamas militants target Israel
description: Rockets have been fired from Gaza "across southern and central Israel, including Tel Aviv and Jerusalem, and the infiltration of Hamas militants."

title: A 5.9-magnitude earthquake shakes southern Mexico but without immediate reports of damage
description: A 5.9-magnitude earthquake has shaken southern Mexico Friday night, setting off alarms as far away as Mexico City, but without immediate reports of damage

title: Israel says Palestinian militants are infiltrating from Gaza. Residents are told to remain indoors
description: The Israeli military says that a number of Palestinian militants have infiltrated into Israel from the Gaza Strip

title: 2 teens indicted on murder, battery charges in fatal hit-and-run of bicyclist captured on video
description: Two teenagers have been indicted and charged as adults with several felonies, including murder and auto theft, after allegedly recording the moment they targeted and fatally struck a bicyclist in a hit-and-run in Las Vegas

title: WATCH:  Rare 8-month-old Javan rhino caught on video
description: A critically endangered 8-month Javan rhino calf was discovered in Indonesia. According to the World Wildlife Fund, they're the world's "most threatened" species of rhino with only around 80 living.
